                    <state type="martyr" source="#bib1098-1">
                        <p>Martyr</p>
                    </state>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1098-1">AMS, II, 250- 53 (fragment) et introduction, IX n° 3 ; BHO, 6;
Suhadii', II, 297-300.
Theodoret, Hist. eccl. xxxix.1- 11, ed. L. Parmentier (Leipzig, 1911), 342-44 ; Hoffmann,
Ausziige, 34-35.
DHGE, I, col. 61- 62, s.v. 1. Abdas.
BS, I, 40- 42 (G. Lucchesi).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract">Afrēm was a Persian Martyr and scribe martyred under shah Yazdegerd with companions <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1097">'Abda</persName>, Jacob, Papa the deacon, Daduq and Durtan the learned.</note>
                    <event type="veneration" source="#bib1098-1">
                        <desc>The saint is venerated on Mar 31 (East Syrian).</desc>
                    </event>
                    <note type="disambiguation">persian martyr, goes with Abda, Hachou, Isaac</note>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1098-1" source="#bib1098-1">
                        <p xml:lang="en">Afrēm is commemorated in <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/340">Abda, Hasho, Isaac, Ephrem, Papa, Dadouq, Dourtan and Papa (text)</title>.</p>
                    </event>
